@Node "HNT" "Hints 'n Tips"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Frequently questions@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
@{i}   - I configured the program to create copies of old files due replace by new ones (function "Backup Copy"). But it doesn't work if I re-write files...
@{ui}
Before replace file some programs (such as DirectoryOpus 4.x) delete old file, and only after it write new one. In this case try to use function "Anti Delete".


@{i}   - After change some parameters in Editor field I press button "Use". But program continues to use old settings...
@{ui}
First press button "Accept" to insert new changes into Patterns list. After it press button "Use".


@{i}   - Patterns in which quotation marks are used, don't work...
@{ui}
Don't use quotation marks in Pattern even if the file or path name has space(s).


@{i}   - Patterns configured for mode "Path" don't work...
@{ui}
Check if pattern string has 'slash' at the end. If has then delete this sign.
@EndNode
@Node "DSC" "Description"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Description and scope of employment@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    As for now the program @{b}AmiMirror@{ub} has three features: creation of spare copies of saved files, backuping rewritten files and preservation of deleted files. All these operations work "on the fly".

   Duplicate of saved files allows to support of a "mirror system". In this mode the saved file is automatically wrote not into one path but in two - the second path you can configurate yourself. By this feature you can get duplicate copies of all saved files needed for you. For example this function may be useful for users who have a removable hard drives and also in systems which provide high safe file storing by creation of spare copies.

   Backup of rewritten files allows to preserve files which are rewritten by any program. By other words, the old file will be automatically backuped into path configurated by you before replaced with new one. This function may be useful if you need to preserve any temporal files (work texts, modified settings etc).

   Preservation of deleted files allows to backup files which are deleted by any program. In this case deleted file will be automatically preserved into path configurated by you before deleted. This function is like some programs which have option "Un Delete". However there is serious different: program @{b}AmiMirror@{ub} preserves deleted files "on the fly", i.e. you will not need to scan disk, check file system structure etc. As result it gives 100 percent preserving of deleted files and there isn't any limitation to use this function with "non-standard" file systems.

   Program @{b}AmiMirror@{ub} works in background mode, i.e. all duplications and backups of files are done automatically. You will not need to run any other software if you want to make copies of saved, rewritten or deleted files because these copies are created "on the fly" while disk operations.

   Program @{b}AmiMirror@{ub} supports not only simple creation of copies of saved and backuped files, but also may use file packing of the popular kit XPK.

   Program @{b}AmiMirror@{ub} is a commodity, i.e. one may be run at any time and controlled by any commodity control program (for example, Exchange).

   Program @{b}AmiMirrorPrefs@{ub} is designed to configure many parameters of the @{b}AmiMirror@{ub} program. It uses the @{" MUI " Link "MUI"} interface.
@EndNode
@Node "INSTALL" "Installation"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Program installation@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    There is no hard-to-install software. The program @{b}AmiMirror@{ub} may be placed in the directory WbStartup.
The program @{b}AmiMirrorPrefs@{ub} may be placed in the directory SYS:Prefs or anywhere you wish. So that the preferences are called correctly from the commodities control program there is a tooltype in the program icon called PREFS which describes the full path of the preferences program. For example:

PREFS=SYS:Prefs/AmiMirrorPrefs

   For further use of this procedure read the chapter @{" use " Link "USG"} program.
@EndNode
@Node "USG" "Usage"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Program usage@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    Before use the program must be @{" installed " Link "INSTALL"}.

   Use of the program @{b}AmiMirror@{ub} is like any other normal program; it's not hard - you need only to run it ;)

   Any configuration of program @{b}AmiMirror@{ub} may be done by preferences editor program @{b}AmiMirrorPrefs@{ub}. You may read about full description of settings' elements in corresponding chapters.

   You may control the program @{b}AmiMirrorPrefs@{ub} either by mouse or keyboard. To control it from the keyboard, select any gadget by pressing the TAB key one or more times. Afterwards use special control keys (as a rule the cursor keys, Enter, and Space) to control it.

   And so, @{b}AmiMirrorPrefs@{ub} has two windows: the main program window and the XPK settings window.

   The main window is divided into two fields - left and right. The left field contains @{" Patterns List " Link "PLS"}, and the right - @{" Editor " Link "EDT"}. By program menu you also can see @{" Program Information " Link "PRI"} or @{" System Information " Link "SYI"}.

   The XPK settings window also has some fields: @{" Packers List " Link "XPL"}, @{" Packer Information " Link "XPI"} and @{" Packer Settings " Link "EDP"}.

   Additionally, in the bottom of main window there are some buttons:

@{b}Save@{ub} - for permanently saving the settings;
@{b}Use@{ub}  - for temporary use of settings;
@{b}Quit@{ub} - quit from program without using or saving the settings.
@EndNode
@Node "PLS" "Patterns List"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Patterns List@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This list shows all configured patterns. I must note that the configuration of patterns may be quite varied. It's described in chapter @{" Editor " Link "EDT"}.

   As a general rule the patterns themselves determine if it is necessary to make a spare/backup copy of a file or not. To edit any pattern from the list simply select one with the mouse or keyboard.

   Additionally, in the bottom of the list there are some buttons:

@{b}Add@{ub}    - to create a new pattern;
@{b}Delete@{ub} - to delete a selected pattern;
@{b}Up@{ub}     - to move up a selected pattern;
@{b}Down@{ub}   - to move down a selected pattern.
@EndNode
@Node "EDT" "Editor"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Editor@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This field of the main window contains many elements, with which you are able to fully configure the operation of @{b}AmiMirror@{ub}.

   Editoring elements are described in the following chapters:

@{" Pattern        " Link "EPT"}
@{" Storage        " Link "EST"}

@{" Function       " Link "FNK"}
@{" Pattern Mode   " Link "EMP"}
@{" Storage Mode   " Link "EMS"}
@{" Storage Method " Link "ETS"}
@{" Perform Check  " Link "EPC"}
@{" Use XPK        " Link "EUX"}

   Additionally, at the bottom of the field there are these buttons:

@{b}Accept@{ub} - to accept changes made in the Editor;
@{b}Cancel@{ub} - to cancel changes.
@EndNode
@Node "EPT" "Pattern"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Pattern configuration@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This is the main parameter of the settings. Any saved, rewritten or deleted file will be compared with patterns you have configured. According to the results of the comparison @{b}AmiMirror@{ub} will make a conclusion about the necessity of making a spare/backup copy of the file. These patterns are set out and described in any AmigaDOS manual. For additional information refer to the appropriate documentation.

   There are some additional requirements to configure its parameters:

   If the Kickstart version is below 3.0 then use only capital letters here.

   If you also indicate here the file path, then use the REAL NAME of disk instead of the device or the assign name, for example use SYSTEM: and not DH0:, SYSTEM:MUI and not MUI:

   DONT use here quotation marks even if the file or path name has space(s) !

   This configuration parameter is also associated with the @{" Pattern Mode " Link "EMP"} and @{" Function " Link "FNK"} parameters.
@EndNode
@Node "EMP" "Pattern Mode"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Pattern Mode@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    It parameter specifies the information of the @{" Pattern " Link "EPT"}.

   This parameter may have the following values:

@{b}Name@{ub}

   This value means that the indicated Pattern is for comparison with the name of the saved, rewritten or deleted file. In this case the path of the file will be ignored. For example, if you select pattern  *.a then any saved, rewritten or deleted file which matches the pattern will be copied/backuped into Storage.

@{b}Path@{ub}

   This value means that the indicated Pattern is to be compared with the path of the saved, rewritten or deleted file, regardless of the name of the file. For example, if you select pattern as WORK:Prefs then any file which is saved, rewritten or deleted in this directory will be copied/backuped into Storage.

@{b}Path & Name@{ub}

   This value means that indicated Pattern is for comparison both with the path and the name of the saved, rewritten or deleted file. For example, if you select pattern  WORK:*.a then any file which is saved, rewritten or deleted in a directory of volume WORK and has extension 'a' will be copied/backuped to Storage.
@EndNode
@Node "FNK" "Function"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Select of work function@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    It parameter specifies the information of the @{" Pattern " Link "EPT"}.

   This parameter may have the following values:

@{b}Spare Copy@{ub}

   This value means that the indicated Pattern is for comparison which is used for create spare copies of saved files.

@{b}Backup Copy@{ub}

   This value means that the indicated Pattern is for comparison which is used for create backup copies of rewritten files.

@{b}Anti Delete@{ub}

   This value means that the indicated Pattern is for comparison which is used for create preserve copies of deleted files.
@EndNode
@Node "EST" "Storage"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Storage configuration@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This parameter indicates the place where copies of saved, rewritten or deleted files will be created.

   This parameter is examined by @{b}AmiMirror@{ub} as the path for the storage location. Accordingly with it you may indicate here any disk, assign or directory name.

   This parameter is also related to parameters @{" Storage Mode " Link "EMS"}, @{" Storage Method " Link "ETS"} and @{" Perform Check " Link "EPC"}.
@EndNode
@Node "EMS" "Storage Mode"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Storage Mode@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This parameter specifies the information of @{" Storage " Link "EST"}.

   This parameter may have the following values:

@{b}Simple File@{ub}

   This value means that a copy of the saved, rewritten or deleted file will be placed in a directory selected in @{" Storage " Link "EST"}. Sometimes it may not be convenient, for example, if you set @{" Pattern Mode " Link "EMP"} as 'Name' because in this case any saved, rewritten or deleted files will be thrown into one directory, which makes it harder to find out from where a given file was copied/backuped. In this case it is preferable to use the following value:

@{b}File & Path@{ub}

   This value means that a copy of the saved, rewritten or deleted file will be placed in an separate directory. Its full path directory is deduced from the path in @{" Storage " Link "EST"} and the path of the saved, rewritten or deleted file. For example, if you select Storage as "BACKDISK:" and the saved, rewritten or deleted file is in the directory "WORK:Tools", then the copy of the file will be written to the directory "BACKDISK:WORK/Tools".
@EndNode
@Node "ETS" "Storage Method"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Storage Method@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This parameter specifies the information of @{" Storage " Link "EST"}.

   This parameter may have the following values:

@{b}Replace@{ub}

   This value means that the copy of the saved, rewritten or deleted file will replace the old file of the same name in Storage, if it exists. Therefore there always will be just one extra copy of the file, the one which was last saved, rewritten or deleted.

@{b}Storage@{ub}

   This value means that a copy of the file saved, rewritten or deleted will be placed in Storage by replacement. In case a file with this name already exists in Storage then it will be given the suffix 0. Accordingly, if there is already a file with suffix 0, then it will be then be given a suffix of 1, and so forth. In this way old file(s) with the same name in Storage will be renamed with extensions 0...99. The current limitation of the number of these files is 100 + 1.
@EndNode
@Node "EPC" "Perform Check"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Perform Check@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This parameter specifies the information of @{" Storage " Link "EST"}.

   If you turn on "Perform Check" then the contents of the saved, rewritten or deleted file will be compared with one of an existing file in Storage. If they are identical then no spare/backup copy will be made by @{b}AmiMirror@{ub}. In other words, this option indicates to @{b}AmiMirror@{ub} from the start what of the file's content needs to be compared, and if they are not different, there is no need to save a copy of the file.
@EndNode
@Node "EUX" "Use of XPK"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Use XPK@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This parameter indicates the need to use and the packer type from the XPK kit. When using XPK packing you may save some space in Storage. On the other hand using a packer decrease the speed of @{b}AmiMirror@{ub} somewhat and increases the requirements for free memory.

For more information about configuring XPK read the chapters which describe the XPK settings window: @{" Packers List " Link "XPL"}, @{" Packer Information " Link "XPI"} and @{" Packer Settings " Link "EDP"}.
@EndNode
@Node "PRI" "Program Information"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Program Information@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This field of the Main Window shows information about the author of the software and some other things.
@EndNode
@Node "SYI" "System Information"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}System Information@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This field of the Main Window shows information about your Amiga: CPU, FPU, free memory, etc.
@EndNode
@Node "XPL" "Packers List"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Packers List@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This field in the XPK settings window shows XPK packers available for use. To select any packer from the list simply select one with the mouse or keyboard. Then the field @{" Packer Information " Link "XPI"} shows information about the selected packer.
@EndNode
@Node "XPI" "Packer Information"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Packer Information@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This field of the XPK settings window shows much information about the selected packer. It describes some parameters:
@{jcenter}
@{b}Encrypt@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   This parameter indicates if the selected packer supports the encryption or not. If so, then this field also shows if a password needs to be used for encryption. Note that if a password is needed then you must indicate one in parameter 'Password' of field @{" Packer Settings " Link "EDP"} !
@{jcenter}
@{b}Ratio@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   The average percentage indicating the degree of compression.
@EndNode
@Node "EDP" "Packer Settings"
@{jcenter}
@{fg highlight}@{b}Packer Settings@{fg text}@{bg back}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}    This field of the XPK settings window lets you configure the parameters of the XPK packer. There are two parameters here:
@{jcenter}
@{b}Step@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   A number actually reflecting the mode of operation of the packer (encryption algorithm, degree of compression, etc).
@{jcenter}
@{b}Password@{ub}
@{jleft}@{lindent 1}
   A word used as a password for encryption if the selected packer supports it. Note that if the parameter 'Encrypt' of field @{" Packer Information " Link "XPI"} shows 'Need Password' then you must fill in the string! Current limitation of length of password is 32 characters.
@EndNode
